post_text:
Tahlequah Families,

We have been informed of a student who has tested positive for COVID-19 at the High School. This student had limited contact on campus last week. 4 other students and 1 teacher came into close contact with this student. These 6 individuals will be quarantined for 14 days as required by the State and Cherokee County Health Dept. All individuals who came into close contact were personally notified, if you did not receive a personal notification your child did not come into contact with the individual. I want to remind all of our parents that the quarantine period is NOT an option, it is mandated by the State Health Department and a negative test CANNOT take the place of a 14-day quarantine. We continue to work closely with the State and Cherokee County Health Department to implement their guidance on minimizing the spread of COVID-19.

Thank you.

post_text:
Tahlequah Families,

We have been informed of a staff member at Greenwood Elementary that has tested positive for COVID-19. Through contact tracing, we have identified 1 additional staff member who came into close contact with this individual. Both staff members will begin immediate quarantine per State and Cherokee Health Department guidelines. These staff members were not in a traditional classroom setting Thursday or Friday, so they did NOT come into close contact (6ft or closer for more than 15 minutes) with any students. This incident will only require the quarantine of the 2 staff members, so it will NOT affect the return of students on Wednesday, Sept. 2nd. We continue to work closely with the State and Cherokee County Health Department to implement their guidance on minimizing the spread of COVID-19.

Thank you

post_text:
Tiger family,

It is with a heavy heart that I announce the passing of one of our teachers. Losing a member of your family is never easy and in the current climate, it makes the situation even worse. We extend our sympathy to the family and our staff.

Out of respect for the family and my staff, we will transition all face to face traditional PK-12 students to ‚Äúdistance learning‚Äù on Monday and Tuesday. If you are a virtual student nothing will change for you. Again, no students will be on campus for classes this Monday and Tuesday, students will return Wednesday, September 2.

All staff will report to work Monday and Tuesday and transition to distance learning for both school days. We will be lenient and understanding with any family who has difficulty with distance learning since we have only been in session 2 days.

Counseling services will be provided for staff and students this week as well.

Thank you in advance for your understanding and cooperation.

Beginning Thursday, August 13th until Wednesday, August 26th, we will be offering free meals to all children 18 years old and under! Please use the back entrance (bus entrance) at Heritage. Students do not have to be present to receive meals (parent/guardian will be asked to provide the names of children they are picking up meals for). We will also deliver to Gardenwalk Apartments and Fox Mobile Homes, Monday through Friday 11:30 am - 12:30 pm. A breakfast and lunch will be given each day. We look forward to serving you!

post_text:
Parents,

Due to the unprecedented times we are in, we have decided to delay the start of school for students until Thursday, August 27, 2020. This will give us time to better prepare our staff for the challenges of education in the COVID pandemic.

Contractually our teachers do not report until Monday, August 10, 2020. We feel that 3 days is not enough to prepare them for the giant task in front of them. We are also experiencing delays in receiving needed technology, PPE and other required essentials to open our school safely.

We will provide an updated calendar once it has been approved by the Board of Education.

Thank you for your understanding

Tahlequah Public Schools is working towards becoming paperless!
All parents/guardians will need to have a guardian portal login for the Wengage system. This will allow you to fill out the necessary documents for the 2020-2021 school year.

The following steps are not necessary if you already have a guardian portal log in.

If you need to request a login: Click the link below, fill out the form, and submit. You will receive and email response with further information.
If you have forgotten your login information please contact Mandy Quantie at 918-458-4100 or quantiem@tahlequahschools.org

We appreciate your cooperation and we look forward to working with our families for the 2020-2021 school year.

Request for guardian portal login:
https://forms.gle/zhS7yAPmGsDANtFU9



Thank you,

Good Morning Tahlequah Tiger Community, Last night the Tahlequah Board of Education approved 3 back to school options for families to choose from:

1. Traditional return to school with 11 distance learning days incorporated into the calendar.
2. A full virtual option
3. A full virtual option with the option of participating in extracurricular activities

We would like the community‚Äôs feedback on what day would be the best to have the distance learning day in the traditional option. The choices are Wednesday and Friday. On distance learning days students will stay home and engage in learning via a digital platform. This will allow them to practice the skills needed in the event a large scale shut down is required. This will also reduce the time they are in contact with others and allow more extensive cleaning to be done. There is a one question survey link below, please choose which day you would prefer.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/399PZBW

Thank you,

Tahlequah Public Schools Child Nutrition
June 8 at 10:44 AM ¬∑

UPDATE:
Due to the overwhelming participation in our curbside meal service at Cherokee Elementary, we have extended our service times. We hope this will alleviate the traffic situation and waiting times. We have also increased the number of meals we will have available. The new service times are for Cherokee Elementary only, Gardenwalk and Fox delivery times will remain the same. All children 18 and under are eligible to receive free meals and do not have to be present to pick up meals. Every Thursday we will provide 5 days worth of meals to each child. Thank you for participating and we look forward to serving you!

WHEN and WHERE: Cherokee Elementary, every Thursday in June and July, curbside delivery 10:00 am - 1:00 pm.

Gardenwalk Apartments, every Thursday in June and July, 11:30 am - 12:30 pm.

Fox Mobile Homes, every Thursday in June and July, 11:30 am - 12:30 pm.

As always, if you have questions please call the Child Nutrition Office @ 918-458-4193.

Good Morning,

Not much has changed but I want to provide you with an update.

1. As of today, school will not be in session until April 6.
2. As with everything that date could change, we will follow the guidance from the Oklahoma State Department of Education.
3. As of today, all school activities are cancelled until April 6.
4. OSSAA and the state will decide if any playoff games will go forward at a later date.
5. TPS will be providing lunches Monday-Friday during the shut-down. The places and times are listed at tahlequahschools.org and on our Facebook page.
6. As of today, no decisions have been made regarding events after April 6. Sports, trips, prom, graduation etc. I hope we can continue will all or some of these events, but at this time we do not know. It is a fluid situation and we will update you if things change.
7. If you need anything or have questions we have administrative staff available to answer phone calls from 8:00 ‚Äì 3:00 each day during the shut-down.

Leon Ashlock
Superintendent
Tahlequah Public Schools

post_text:
Starting Monday March 23 until Friday April 3 School will be closed to students as directed by the state of Oklahoma.

During this time teachers and support staff will not be reporting to work. However, all of our sites will be open from 8:00-3:00 Monday through Friday if you need anything. Our administrative staff will be available and reporting to work during the shutdown.

We will be providing lunch Monday -Friday during the shutdown at the locations listed on our website at www.tahlequahschools.org or on our Facebook Page. During lunch delivery times some sites may not be open because our administration staff will be handling the food deliveries, so please be patient if you need something during this time frame.

text:
Starting Monday March 23 until Friday April 3 School will be closed to students as directed by the state of Oklahoma.

During this time teachers and support staff will not be reporting to work. However, all of our sites will be open from 8:00-3:00 Monday through Friday if you need anything. Our administrative staff will be available and reporting to work during the shutdown.

We will be providing lunch Monday -Friday during the shutdown at the locations listed on our website at www.tahlequahschools.org or on our Facebook Page. During lunch delivery times some sites may not be open because our administration staff will be handling the food deliveries, so please be patient if you need something during this time frame.

TAHLEQUAHSCHOOLS.ORG
Tahlequah Public Schools

post_text:
Beginning Monday, March 23, 2020, Tahlequah Public Schools will offer lunch Monday through Friday at the following locations:

11:30-12:30 Cherokee Elementary School ‚Äì Grab and Go. Families will drive in front of the school cafeteria on Ward Street and a meal will be brought out to your car.

11:30 am: Trimble Apartment Complex, Step Mobile Homes, South Breeze Trailer Park, Fox Trailer Park east entrance, Garden Walk laundry mat, North Cedar trailer park

12:00 pm: Twin Oaks apartments on The corner of Allen and Jones, Tahlequah Terrace, Elks Lodge trailer park, Fox trailer park west entrance, Garden Walk back parking lot

Children 18 and below can eat FREE. Child MUST be present to pick up the hot meal. Look for a TPS van or bus!
This institution is an equal opportunity provider.

post_text:
Tahlequah,

As you have probably heard the State Department of Education has extended spring break until April 5.

This means at the very least, TPS students will not return to school until Monday April 6.

I am meeting with district administration staff tonight and throughout the week to plan our next course of action.

We will share plans and updates on Facebook, our website and via all-call messages.

Leon Ashlock
Superintendent
Tahlequah Public Schools.

post_text:
Due to the mounting concerns over the coronavirus and the possibility of exposure to our students and staff, TPS has made the decision to immediately suspend all out of state travel until further notice.

We know trips have been planned, and in some cases already in progress but we see no other option due to a wave of closures and cancellations that started today.

Most schools in the state are adopting the same policy as we speak. All Practices and events now through March 22 will be cancelled or postponed.

Please know these decisions are made with the safety of our students, staff, parents and community in mind.

post_text:
Madilyn is a first-grade student at Cherokee Elementary who loves going to school, Elsa, and drawing. She was diagnosed, for the third time, with a Wilms tumor as well as AML. Madilyn is going to need a transplant and you can help her and other patients in need. Are you 18-44 years old, willing to donate to anyone and in good health? Then join ‚ÄúBe The Match‚Äù. If your tissue type ever matches a patient in need, you will donate to that specific patient. Depending on the need of that patient, you will donate stem cells (like donating platelets, plasma or double red cells) or marrow (special needle used to draw marrow while under anesthesia). You could be the only cure for that patient.
Be committed to saving a life.

January 9, 2020
10:00am ‚Äì 6:00pm
Cherokee Elementary
800 E. Goingsnake
Tahlequah, OK 74464

post_text:
Parents/Guardians- Want to know your student‚Äôs grades and/or missing assignments (4th grade-12th grade)? Want to pay for lunches online?
It‚Äôs EASY! All you need is a password

Step 1- Complete a form: Pick one up from your student‚Äôs school or the Board Office on Water Street or print it from our website.

Form can be located here:

http://www.tahlequahschools.org/vimages/shared/vnews/stories/5446acd034300/pportal.pdf

Step 2- Return the form: To your child‚Äôs school office or the Board Office with a copy of your picture ID (Please plan on allowing a copy of your driver‚Äôs license or ID to go with the form.)
‚Ä¢ Name on the form and ID must match

Step 3- You will receive an email with your username and activation code, PROCESS COMPLETE!

We encourage everyone to do this before Parent Teacher Conferences. During conferences computer labs will be open and there will be someone to help parents get logged in, see grades, attendance and pay lunches if needed. It‚Äôs a great way to stay connected with your child‚Äôs education.

August 16, 2019 at 8:30 AM ¬∑

Reminder: Today is the last day of the district wide charging extension. Beginning Monday, August 19th at breakfast, the charge policy will be in effect. The charge policy states there is a $10 charge limit. If a student owes $10 or more, they will be offered an alternative meal at no charge. Payments can be made to the cafeteria cashiers, on the Wengage parent portal, or at the Child Nutrition Office located at 619 N. Jones. Thank you for your patronage and we look forward to serving your children!

This institution is an equal opportunity provider.

I would like to remind our patrons that the school and community have taken measures to provide some services while school is not in session. Sequoyah Elementary School located on 425 S. College will be providing breakfast and lunch for children under the age of 18 during the Work Stoppage. Please refer to the FAQ or Frequently Asked Questions document on the TPS website and the school‚Äôs Facebook pages for more details about these services and other issues regarding the Work Stoppage.
Notice about school closing will be on the TPS Website at www.tahlequahschools.org, the schools‚Äô Facebook pages and posted on the local television stations.
Again, school will be closed on Monday, April 9. We here at Tahlequah Public Schools can‚Äôt thank you enough for your support!

post_text:
This is Lisa Presley, Superintendent of Tahlequah Public Schools, with an important message about the district closing school on January 4&5. A portion of Heritage Elementary flooded yesterday due to a break in one of the sprinkler systems. Unfortunately, repairs and clean up to the school will require time by the restoration company to fix the damage done by the flooding.
So again, school will be closed district-wide on Thursday and Friday, January 4th and 5th as if these were snow days. Student activities that are scheduled will go on as planned.
We apologize for any inconvenience to families that closing school on Thursday and Friday may cause. Our goal is for school to be back in session on Monday, January 8. Thank you for your patience and have a great day!
text:
This is Lisa Presley, Superintendent of Tahlequah Public Schools, with an important message about the district closing school on January 4&5. A portion of Heritage Elementary flooded yesterday due to a break in one of the sprinkler systems. Unfortunately, repairs and clean up to the school will require time by the restoration company to fix the damage done by the flooding.
So again, school will be closed district-wide on Thursday and Friday, January 4th and 5th as if these were snow days. Student activities that are scheduled will go on as planned.
We apologize for any inconvenience to families that closing school on Thursday and Friday may cause. Our goal is for school to be back in session on Monday, January 8. Thank you for your patience and have a great day!

post_text:
This message is to inform families of Tahlequah Public School students that a social media threat has been received by a middle school student targeted for today, Oct. 6. Other threats have occurred county-wide and are being investigated by local law enforcement.
What we know right now is that the threat was targeted at Tahlequah Middle School and is also being investigated by our School Resource Officers. The district and local law enforcement are taking the threat seriously. This type of information spreads quickly so we want you to know that our School Resource Officers are on alert and are taking every precaution to keep your children safe.

shared_text:
Tenkiller Public School
February 3, 2016 at 10:18 AM ¬∑ Tahlequah, OK ¬∑

The Cherokee County PLAC (Parent Legislative Action Committee) will be meeting on Thursday, February 25, 6:00 pm, at the Indian Capital Technology Center in the Seminar Room. The topics for discussion will be Education Legislation and the Budget Shortfall. As many of you know, K-8 schools are under attack by the legislature and governor who want consolidation or to close the K-8 schools. Now is the time we need parents the most to become involved in helping save our K-8 schools! Come join us at the PLAC meeting to see how you can help. You can also like the "K-8 Nation Oklahoma" facebook page for updates. If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to ask! Thank you for your support!

We also have had reports of a threatening social media post by a student. The student has been identified and is being dealt with by administration through routine school procedures. Our first priority is student safety. If you have any questions please contact your school principal.
